			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=5105')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&amp;REPLY_ID=57906&amp;TOPIC_ID=6973&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=lifeburn+tricks%3F&amp;M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         FYI if you are putting a lifetap DOT on the mob you intend to lifeburn you are increasing your chances of lifeburn not taking hold and thus killing yourself.</P><P>My best advice to avoid the buggy lifeburn death is to:</P><P>1) communicate with at least the rest of the necros in your raid and try to time your lifeburns so they are not hitting at the same time, and that they are not hitting when the mob is layered with other DOTS.</P><P>2) always put up a manaskin or better before you cast.</P><P>3) never cast lifeburn while you have a lich spell active.</P><P>4) always keep harmshield and/or qvox memmed and cast it immediately after you lifeburn.</P><P>5) get a shaman to torpor you just before you cast lifeburn.</P><P>Personally i have never died to Lifeburn.  I have seen necros die to lifeburn while standing right next to me, usually due to aggro and either not using harmshield immediately after or just being really unlucky on the summon cycle.  I have probably cast life burn ~ 30 or 40 times now.</P><P>Once i have seen a necro die due to Lifeburn not taking hold.  We determined that this was most likely due to all the buff slots being filled on the target mob at the time.</P><P>I have cast life burn on a mob immediately after another necro casts life burn on the same mob ( Emperor Ssra ) and i DID NOT get the spell did not take hold message.  Lifeburn landed for full, the dot took hold and i lived.</P><P>Going out on a limb here, i know many of you say that when life burn kills you due to effect not taking hold on target that it is an instant and unavoidable death.  However, the necros i have talked to that have had this happen to them all tell me the same thing.  Life burn hits the mob, casting necro is reduced to 1 hit point, Life Burn does not take hold on mob, THEN necro is killed by himself.  The one and only time i have witnessed this happen to another necro he died from Arch Lich after he was lowered to 1 hit point.  If he had gotten a heal and not had Arch Lich up, i believe he would have lived.  If he had a rune in place before he cast life burn i believe he would have lived also.</P><P>Flame on.. i know you are all going to tell i am full of shit about this last part, but being as i have yet to lose my life to Life Burn i am trying to figure out what the rest of you are doing wrong =p</P><P>Vtyn</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
